[{"id":"VH911211","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of the crystal structure of N a B r. The diagram consists of a cube formed from alternating larger shaded circles and smaller unshaded circles that are tightly packed, with almost no space between them.\" height=\"140\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH911211.g01.png\" width=\"155\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The crystal structure of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is represented in the diagram above. Which statement correctly compares crystalline <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r, solid\"><math alttext=\"N a B r, solid\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to molten <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r, liquid\"><math alttext=\"N a B r, liquid\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> in terms of electrical conductivity?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH911211_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Crystalline <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> contains no freely moving electrons that could conduct an electrical current, whereas electrons can flow freely in molten <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, which is a good conductor of electricity.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Crystalline <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and molten <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> both contain ions that are held in fixed positions due to strong electrostatic attractions among the ions, making neither a good electrical conductor.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Crystalline <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and molten <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> both contain <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a\"><math alttext=\"N a\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Na</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> atoms that transfer electrons to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B r\"><math alttext=\"B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Br</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> atoms in a chemical reaction, thus allowing them both to be good conductors of electricity.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Crystalline <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> contains no freely moving electrons to conduct electricity, but molten <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a B r\"><math alttext=\"N a B r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>NaBr</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is composed of freely moving <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a with a positive one charge\"><math alttext=\"N a with a positive one charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Na</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B r with a negative one charge\"><math alttext=\"B r with a negative one charge\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Br</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>âˆ’</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ions, which allows it to be a good conductor of electricity.</p>"],"answer":3}]